The paper focuses on physical adversarial attacks on object detectors, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning an adversarial pattern, which can be achieved through machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the optimization constraint to make the generated patterns look natural for human observers, which is related to computer graphics (cs.MM). Finally, the paper addresses the security aspect of object detectors, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR).
